                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 **Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference (SCIAC)**

The [Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference](/Southern_California_Intercollegiate_Athletic_Conference) (SCIAC) is a prominent collegiate athletic league that functions within the framework of the [NCAA's Division III](/NCAA_Division_Athletic_Association). Established in 1915, the conference serves as a competitive home for twelve distinct, predominantly smaller private academic institutions, all strategically situated across the vibrant expanse of [Southern California](/Southern_California). These institutions, while individually unique, consolidate their athletic efforts into nine distinct programs. This organizational structure is particularly notable in the instances of [Claremont-Mudd-Scripps](/Claremont-Mudd-Scripps_Stags_and_Athenas) and [Pomona-Pitzer](/Pomona-Pitzer_Sagehens), which operate as combined teams for the purposes of intercollegiate sports.

The SCIAC, under the leadership of Commissioner Jennifer Dubow, boasts an impressive and comprehensive athletic offering, sponsoring a total of 21 sports. This includes 10 distinct men's sports and 11 distinct women's sports, ensuring a broad spectrum of athletic engagement for its student-athletes.

**Sports Currently Sponsored by the SCIAC:**

*   **Men's Sports:** [Baseball](/Baseball), [Basketball](/Basketball), [Cross Country](/Cross_country_running), [Football](/American_football), [Golf](/Golf), [Soccer](/Soccer), [Swimming and Diving](/Swimming_(sport)), [Tennis](/Tennis), [Track and Field](/Track_and_field), and [Water Polo](/Water_Polo).
*   **Women's Sports:** [Basketball](/Basketball), [Cross Country](/Cross_country_running), [Golf](/Golf), [Lacrosse](/Lacrosse), [Soccer](/Soccer), [Softball](/Softball), [Swimming and Diving](/Diving_(sport)), [Tennis](/Tennis), [Track and Field](/Track_and_field), [Volleyball](/Volleyball), and [Water Polo](/Water_Polo).

The conference headquarters are located in [Laguna Niguel, California](/Laguna_Niguel,_California), anchoring its administrative operations within the very region its member institutions call home. As of the current academic year, the SCIAC consists of 9 teams, a number set to expand to 10 in 2026, signaling a continued evolution and commitment to growth in the collegiate athletic landscape. For those seeking further information, the official website, thesciac.org, serves as the primary digital portal.

